The paper discusses the security and privacy challenges associated with the use of machine learning in healthcare applications, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the application of machine learning techniques in healthcare, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses computer-aided diagnosis (CADx) using medical images, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges associated with ensuring privacy in healthcare settings, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential methods to ensure secure and privacy-preserving ML for healthcare applications, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category.
